title: Not I, But Christ
author: Mrs. Ada A. Whiddington (1891)
presentation: v1 c v2 c v3 c v4 c v5 c

v1: Not I, but Christ be honored, loved, exalted,
Not I, but Christ be seen, be known be heard;
Not I, but Christ in every look and action,
Not I, but Christ in every thought and word.
v2: Not I, but Christ to gently soothe in sorrow,
Not I, but Christ to wipe the falling tear;
Not I, but Christ to lift the weary burden,
Not I, but Christ to hush away all fear.
v3: Christ, only Christ, no idle word e'er falling,
Christ, only Christ, no needless bustling sound;
Christ, only Christ, no self important bearing,
Christ, only Christ, no trace of "I" be found.
v4: Not I, but Christ my every need supplying,
Not I, but Christ my strength and health to be;
Christ, only Christ, for body, soul and spirit,
Christ, only Christ, live then Thy life in me.
v5: Christ, only Christ, ere long will fill my vision,
Glory excelling soon, full soon I'll see;
Christ, only Christ, my every wish fulfilling,
Christ, only Christ, my all in all to be.
c1: Oh, to be saved from myself, dear Lord,
Oh, to be lost in Thee.
Oh, that it may be no more I,
But Christ that lives in me.
